aa(lp445
VLet me say one last comment.
p446
aVIf you think about Adam Smith versus Karl Marx,
p447
aVAdam Smith had a very important notion of efficiency.
p448
aVHe gave an example of a pin factory.
p449
aVHe said pins have 12 different steps,
p450
aVand if one person does all 12 steps, production is very low.
p451
aVBut if you get one person to do step one,
p452
aVand one person to do step two and step three and so on,
p453
aVproduction can increase tremendously.
p454
aVAnd indeed, this is a great example,
p455
aVand the reason for the Industrial Revolution and efficiency.
p456
aVKarl Marx, on the other hand,
p457
aVsaid that the alienation of labor is incredibly important
p458
aVin how people think about the connection to what they are doing.
p459
aVAnd if you do all 12 steps, you care about the pin.
p460
aVBut if you do one step every time, maybe you don't care as much.
p461
aa(lp462
VI think that in the Industrial Revolution,
p463
aVAdam Smith was more correct than Karl Marx.
p464
aVBut the reality is that we've switched,
p465
aVand now we're in the knowledge economy.
p466
aVYou can ask yourself, what happens in a knowledge economy?
p467
aVIs efficiency still more important than meaning?
p468
aVI think the answer is no.
p469
aVI think that as we move to situations
p470
aVin which people have to decide on their own
p471
aVabout how much effort, attention, caring, how connected they feel to it,
p472
aVare they thinking about labor on the way to work,
p473
aVand in the shower and so on,
p474
aVall of a sudden Marx has more things to say to us.
p475
aVSo when we think about labor,
p476
aVwe usually think about motivation and payment as the same thing,
p477
aVbut the reality is that we should probably add all kinds of things to it \u2014
p478
aVmeaning, creation, challenges, ownership, identity, pride, etc.
p479
aa(lp480
VThe good news is that if we added all of those components
p481
aVand thought about them \u2014
p482
aVhow do we create our own meaning, pride, motivation,
